The article discusses anonymous evaluations of Judge Brett Kavanaugh, President Trump's Supreme Court nominee, by his law students at Harvard, Yale, and Georgetown. The evaluations overwhelmingly praise Kavanaugh's teaching abilities, mastery of legal materials, intellectual rigor, fair-mindedness, and accessibility. Many students consider him to be the most impressive law school professor they have encountered. Despite a perceived conservative bias in his class enrollment, students appreciate Kavanaugh's evenhandedness and his acceptance of views across the political spectrum. His classes at Harvard were three hours long and included discussions of current events, office hours, and social events with students. Former students describe him as a rigorous thinker, devoted teacher, and gracious person. Kavanaugh's class at Yale on national security law also received high praise from students.